{
  "stem": "25381.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the whole family were very nice, polite.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So we were OK.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We lived in a neighborhood that-- mixed neighborhood.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was Ukrainian, Polish, and Jewish-- mostly, majority Ukrainian people and Polish and Jewish.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We were very nice.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We had nice neighbors.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were-- from the beginning-- they were very, very nice to us.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They respected my mother.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "She-- she loved them very much and we were like-- they respected her very-- very well, my mother.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Before the war, no.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We did not.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I went to school-- I went to Polish school-- and it used to come-- after Polish school, I went to Heder, to Hebrew-- Hebrew school.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And once a weak used to come a Catholic Pope to give an hour, you know, religious day.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So as Jewish kids, we could have stayed if we wanted.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We didn't have to home.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So sometimes, we went home.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Sometimes, for instance, me, myself, I went home.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And sometimes I stayed there in the class.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I was interested to hear this.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And they used to-- you know, they said the-- the Polish prayer-- [POLISH].",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then they said-- and then once a week, it came the Ukrainian.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The-- the-- the Polish, they called [POLISH].",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The Ukrainian, they called pope.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I learned how to say the Ukrainian, the prayer, like [UKRAINIAN]. .",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I still remember up till now, and that helped me a lot to survive, that-- that [UKRAINIAN], that means the prayer.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And should I talk more about that?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we were very nice.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Went to school.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was a very nice town.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was a small city, not big, but like a 200 Jewish families.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But it was very warm and friendly, and my mother were a lovely lady.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Everybody respect her very well.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
